# Supabase → AWS Migration Procedure

## Goal

Migrate from Supabase-managed PostgreSQL to AWS-hosted PostgreSQL while preserving:

- schema
- data
- indexes
- extensions
- functions
- RLS policies (optional)
- application compatibility

Typical AWS targets:
- Amazon RDS PostgreSQL
- Aurora PostgreSQL
- self-managed PostgreSQL on EC2

RECOMMENDED:
Use Amazon RDS PostgreSQL.

---

# Recommended Architecture

| Environment | Infrastructure |
|---|---|
| Frontend | Vercel / AWS Amplify |
| Database | AWS RDS PostgreSQL |
| Auth | Supabase Auth OR Auth.js/Clerk/Cognito |
| Storage | AWS S3 |
| Realtime | Supabase Realtime OR custom |
| Functions | AWS Lambda |

---

# Important Reality Check

Supabase is NOT only PostgreSQL.

Supabase also provides:
- Auth
- Storage
- Realtime
- Edge Functions
- API generation
- RLS helpers

Migrating ONLY the DB is easy.

Migrating the FULL Supabase stack requires replacing those services.

---

# Migration Options

## Option A — Keep Supabase Services + Move DB to AWS

You:
- migrate PostgreSQL to AWS
- keep frontend auth/storage in Supabase

NOT recommended long-term.

---

## Option B — Full AWS Migration (Recommended)

Replace:
- Supabase DB → RDS PostgreSQL
- Supabase Storage → S3
- Supabase Auth → Cognito/Auth.js/Clerk
- Edge Functions → Lambda

This is the scalable architecture.

---

# 1. Create AWS PostgreSQL Database

## Recommended

Create:

- Amazon RDS PostgreSQL

Go to:

AWS Console → RDS → Create Database

Choose:
- PostgreSQL
- latest stable version
- public access OFF (preferred)
- backup enabled

Save:
- endpoint
- port
- username
- password

Example:

```text
builderlab-db.xxxxxx.eu-west-3.rds.amazonaws.com
```

---

# 2. Export Supabase Schema

Inside project:

```bash
npx supabase db pull
```

OR directly:

```bash
pg_dump \
  --schema-only \
  "SUPABASE_DB_URL" \
  > schema.sql
```

---

# 3. Export Data

## Full DB

```bash
pg_dump \
  --data-only \
  "SUPABASE_DB_URL" \
  > data.sql
```

---

## Recommended: selective export

Example:

```bash
pg_dump \
  --data-only \
  --table=users \
  --table=projects \
  --table=subscriptions \
  "SUPABASE_DB_URL" \
  > data.sql
```

Avoid exporting:
- auth tables
- internal Supabase schemas
- realtime schemas

---

# 4. Create AWS Extensions

Supabase enables extensions automatically.

On AWS RDS you must create them manually.

Common ones:

```sql
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "uuid-ossp";
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS pgcrypto;
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector;
```

Check your Supabase DB:

```sql
SELECT * FROM pg_extension;
```

---

# 5. Import Schema into AWS

```bash
psql \
  -h YOUR_RDS_HOST \
  -U postgres \
  -d postgres \
  < schema.sql
```

---

# 6. Import Data into AWS

```bash
psql \
  -h YOUR_RDS_HOST \
  -U postgres \
  -d postgres \
  < data.sql
```

---

# 7. Remove Supabase-Specific Objects

Supabase creates internal schemas like:

- auth
- storage
- realtime
- supabase_functions

You may:
- keep them temporarily
- or remove them

Usually you should NOT migrate:
- auth schema
- storage schema
- realtime schema

Focus on:
- public schema
- business tables

---

# 8. Update Application Environment Variables

Replace:

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
```

with standard PostgreSQL connection variables:

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/dbname
```

---

# 9. Replace Supabase Client

If currently using:

```ts
import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js'
```

you now need:
- Prisma
- Drizzle
- Kysely
- pg

RECOMMENDED:
Prisma or Drizzle.

---

# Example Prisma Setup

Install:

```bash
npm install prisma @prisma/client
```

Initialize:

```bash
npx prisma init
```

Set:

```env
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...
```

Pull schema:

```bash
npx prisma db pull
```

---

# 10. Storage Migration (Supabase → S3)

If using Supabase Storage:

Create:
- AWS S3 bucket

Then migrate files.

Example sync:

```bash
aws s3 sync ./uploads s3://builderlab-storage
```

Update app upload logic accordingly.

---

# 11. Auth Migration

## If currently using Supabase Auth

You have options:

### Recommended:
- Auth.js
- Clerk
- AWS Cognito

---

# 12. Realtime Migration

Supabase realtime relies on:
- WAL replication
- websockets

AWS alternatives:
- Pusher
- Ably
- Socket.IO
- custom Postgres LISTEN/NOTIFY

---

# 13. Deployment Update

Update:
- Vercel env vars
- Docker secrets
- CI/CD

to use AWS DB credentials.

---

# 14. Verify Migration

Test:
- inserts
- updates
- auth
- uploads
- subscriptions
- cron jobs
- API routes

---

# Recommended Final AWS Stack

| Concern | Recommended |
|---|---|
| DB | AWS RDS PostgreSQL |
| ORM | Prisma |
| Auth | Clerk/Auth.js |
| Storage | S3 |
| CDN | CloudFront |
| Compute | Lambda/ECS |
| Frontend | Vercel or Amplify |

---

# Zero-Downtime Migration Strategy (Recommended)

## Phase 1
- AWS DB created
- data replicated

## Phase 2
- app reads from old DB
- writes dual-write

## Phase 3
- switch primary DB

## Phase 4
- shutdown Supabase DB

